title: Caleb Centanni
text:
About me

PhD student at Lab of Ornithology in Natural Resources field, studying Evening Grosbeaks
Originally from Oregon, where I was an avid birder and have seen more than 400 species
Enjoy writing songs and poetry when not in the field
Excited to be learning programming languages this term!

title: Charadrius Plovers
text:
Family Charadriidae (plovers)
Species: 4
Ranges reflect breeding grounds only.
Killdeer(Charadrius vociferus), Range: Americas from Equatorial Region North
Common Ringed Plover(Charadrius hiaticula), Range: High Boreal Palearctic and Greenland Tundra
Semipalmated Plover(Charadrius semipalmatus), Range: High Boreal Nearctic Tundra Excepting Greenland
Piping Plover(Charadrius melodus), Range: High Temperate Nearctic Sandflats and Beaches

title: Coccothraustes Grosbeaks
text:
Family: Fringillidae (cardueline finches) Species: 3
Hawfinch (Coccothraustes coccothraustes), Range: High Temperate Palearctic



The piercing gaze of a Hawfinch


Evening Grosbeak (Coccothraustes vespertinus), Range: Boreal and Subalpine Nearctic
